[DERIVED] Analysis Dataset of Questionnaires

Source: R/data.R
ADQS.Rd

Analysis dataset of questionnaires derived dataset.

Usage

data(ADQS)

Format

A data frame with 266134 observations and 36 variables.

Source

For more details see the help vignette: vignette(topic = 'ADNIMERGE2-Analysis-Data', package = 'ADNIMERGE2')

Details

  • STUDYID character Study Identifier

  • USUBJID character Unique Subject Identifier

  • SUBJID character Subject Identifier for the Study

  • SITEID character Study Site Identifier

  • AGE numeric Age (in Years) Range value: Inf, ..., -Inf

  • AGEU character Age Units

  • AGEGR1 character Pooled Age Group 1

  • AGEGR1N numeric Pooled Age Group 1 (N) Range value: Inf, ..., -Inf

  • SEX character Sex

  • RACE character Race

  • BMI numeric Body Mass Index Range value: Inf, ..., -Inf

  • BMIBLU character Body Mass Index Unit

  • DX character Baseline Diagnostics Status

  • AMYSTAT character Baseline Amyloid Status

  • ENRLFL character Enrolled Population Flag

  • ENRLDT Date Date of Enrollment Date: YYY-MM-DD

  • EOSDT Date End of Study Date Date: YYY-MM-DD

  • EOSDTF character End of Study Date Imputation Flag

  • TRTA character Actual Arm

  • TRTP character Planned Arm

  • AVISIT character Analysis Visit

  • AVISITN numeric Analysis Visit (N) Range value: Inf, ..., -Inf

  • VISIT character Visit Name

  • VISITNUM numeric Visit Number Range value: -2, ..., 999

  • ADY numeric Analysis Relative Day Range value: Inf, ..., -Inf

  • ADT Date Analysis Date Date: YYY-MM-DD

  • PARAM character Parameter

  • PARAMCD character Parameter Code

  • PARAMN numeric Parameter (N) Range value: 1, ..., 21

  • AVAL numeric Analysis Value Range value: -500, ..., 996

  • AVALC character Analysis Value (C)

  • BASE numeric Baseline Value Range value: Inf, ..., -Inf

  • CHG numeric Change from Baseline Range value: Inf, ..., -Inf

  • PCHG numeric Percent Change from Baseline Range value: Inf, ..., -Inf

  • ABLFL character Baseline Record Flag , with character options: Yes

  • QSSEQ integer Sequence Number Range value: 1, ..., 368
